planetary body all though it is capable of doing this<br>
easily.Orion also is not intended to land on the surface<br>
of a planetary body, all though it could do so easily by<br>
deorbiting itself with a few pu  explosions and then using additional pu  explosions to brake its velocity as it falls toward a planetary surface.  Orion is intended to operate only in<br>
space. The purpose of operating it only in space is to prevent<br>
contamination of a planetary  biosphere by Radioactive fall out et el. This is true for both fission, and fusion powered<br>
versions of Orion. Operating Orion in earth orbit will not<br>
contaminate the Biosphere of earth because the Radioactive<br>
debris created by the pu detonations will have a velocity<br>
of at least 1000 kilometers a second for even small ten kiloton<br>
atomic pulse unit  explosions for example. 1000 kilometers a second is more then 3,000,000 miles per hour. Solar system escape velocity is only 93,500 miles per hour.For this reason<br>
the earths gravity can not capture any of Orions Radioactive debris trail, due the fact that Earth escape  velocity is just<br>
25,000 miles per hour . The Radioactive debris trail from the Orion pu detonations would be traveling 3,000,000 miles per hour on its way completely out of the solar system . <br>
The suns gravity can not capture any radioactive debris either<br>
from the Orion pu explosions  because the debris is traveling must faster then the solar sytem escape velocity of 93,500 miles per hour.<br>
