<br>
Quite simple.<br>
<br>
Match velocity &amp; trajectory with your target asteroid, extend docking bars (sections of truss, built piece by piece in EVA) as the ship &quot;falls&quot; towards the rock at a few tenths of a millimeter per hour.<br>
 When the ship hits (a few days later), the few ergs of energy from the impact are taken up by the docking bars.<br>
<br>
 Oh, you mean on a planet?<br>
 Still simple.<br>
<br>
How to get people from an aircraft carrier to an inland airbase? An imposible task...<br>
<br>
Use some of the Orion ship's mass-carrying capacity to carry a retro-rocket lander.<br>
